    "comment": "Rationale: - CRMP2 (DPYSL2) promotes the dendritic spine maturation in cultured hippocampal neurons.\n- Dephosphorylation of CRMP2 at Thr514 further promotes the dendritic spine maturation.\n- DeSUMOylation of CRMP2 at Lys374 also promotes the dendritic spine maturation.\n- During this process, SUMOylation of CRMP2 is independent of its phosphorylation.. Experimental description: M&M: \"All the experiments were conducted with 1-day old pups of Sprague-Dawley (SD) rats\"\n\n\"The cDNA fragments encoding CRMP2 and SENP1, were amplified by PCR using the obtained clone of rat CRMP2 (NM_001105717.2) and SENP1 (XM_017595316.1) as templates.\"",
